blog.name: angelofberlin2000
blog.title: Like a Rose trampled on the ground
blog.description:
In addition to the pain and the exhaustion, he recalled how waiting on the cross between takes became tedious. To fight the boredom, he listened to music on headphones. One particular song called "Above All" (Like a Rose ...) by Michael W. Smith helped him through his most difficult moments.

"It arrived when I was confused and angry. I didn't think I could go on. The song described how Jesus was rejected and alone. That thought took me to a place — it opened an interior door that held me while on the cross," an emotional Caviezel explained. "The experience of feeling rejected and alone as all those around me laughed while drinking their hot coffees, oblivious to what was occurring. Jesus must have felt like this — forsaken, rejected, alone, and despised. It helped me pray in a very deep way — to pray without words, to pray from the heart. The discomfort, the loneliness, the split shoulder, the raw flesh all forced me into the arms of God because I had nowhere else to go for a performance I knew I was unable to create."
Jim Caviezel, Shamelessly Catholic

blog.name: giographixnola
blog.title: giographix
blog.description: I'm getting too old for this shit. Narcoleptic-Insomniac. Monster. Sinister. Diabetic. I'm transcending the fall from the garden. Damnation dignified. Mono no aware. New Orleans, drinking, video games (mostly Destiny related), vape stuff, art, design, and cats. On occasion, doggos. I post whatever the hell I feel like at the time, I am literally a real life walking shit post. I sometimes post dank memes. Self parody. Midway upon the journey of our life I found myself within a forest dark, for the straightforward pathway had been lost. I should have been a pair of ragged claws, scuttling across the floors of silent seas. Then I saw there was a way to Hell even from the gates of Heaven. My religion is the practice of sedition. Si vis pacem, para bellum. Come to the darkside... we have rum & covfefe. Weltanschauung. Saudade. Se habla Español.

question: watching a walk into the clouds and can I just say I love how much of a sweet DORK Paul is but at the same time I LOVE that he says to his wife’s bf “I’m not going to hit you” and you KNOW that’s a mercy because  he’s an actual weapon (being a soldier and also that it’s Keanu, action movie extraordinaire) who could fully destroy the dude if he wanted to?? i just love it
answer:
Pt 2 Also bless paul because all he wants to do is save the vineyard and they can’t give him a shovel for some reason to dig out the root so he has to rip it out of the earth with his bare hands in a slowmo dramatic shot for Reasons—AND THEN after he gives the love of his life a ring made of a chocolate wrapper because he’s SO SOFT I can’t take it (pardon the rambling haha!)

SAME, ANON, SAME. Paul is so, so sweet and kind and dorky and tbh one of my ultimate favorite Keanu characters–probably because he is similar to Keanu’s own kind and gentle and dorky personality. Paul is EVERYTHING and I love him. He just loves Victoria so much and would do anything for her and???? why is he so perfect??

THIS LINE THO: “Why can’t you just love her? She’s so easy to love.” 

and “I want you more than anything, Victoria. You can’t imagine how I want you.” but he stops kissing her bc he’s still technically married to someone else and he can’t hurt her that way and??? AGH

*cries about paul sutton forever*
